@prefix skos:	<http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
<http://w3id.org/lob/concept/1279>	rdf:type	skos:Concept ;
	skos:broader	<http://w3id.org/lob/concept/1227> ;
	skos:prefLabel	"cut to show proof (bookblocks)"@en ;
	skos:inScheme	<http://w3id.org/lob/> ;
	skos:scopeNote	"Book blocks the edge of which is cut to a depth that leaves the shortest leaves uncut, showing, on handmade paper, the deckle edge of the sheet. This term is specific to books with leaves of handmade-paper. Cutting to show proof was a sign of careful work, and was intended to leave proof (t\u00E9moins in French) that only the minimum amount necessary to leave a clean edge had been removed from the margin of the leaf."@en .